ğŸ”„ Automation Cycle

Every 15 minutes GitHub Actions:

Opens the Google Sheet

Reads new or updated records

Normalizes and validates data

Syncs information into the following DB tables:

-owners

-cats

-bookings

-vaccinations

-services

Writes sync results back into Google Sheets (kayit_durumu & hata_mesaj)

ğŸ§  Features
ğŸ”¹ 1. Owner & Pet Management

Owners are uniquely identified by (name, phone number)

Multiple cats under the same owner are supported

Cat records auto-update if edited in Google Sheets

ğŸ”¹ 2. Booking Management

Each booking receives a persistent booking_id

Edits in the sheet update the existing database record

Supports date parsing, numeric normalization, and data cleaning

ğŸ”¹ 3. Vaccination Tracking

New vaccine entries are appended to the vaccinations table

Historical vaccination records remain visible in the database

Google Sheets only shows the latest dates

ğŸ”¹ 4. Service Tracking

Pet taxi usage is tracked

Ensures 1-to-1 relationship per booking

ğŸ” Security

.env remains local and is never pushed to GitHub

Supabase credentials & Google Service Account JSON
are stored securely inside GitHub Secrets

JSON authentication file is generated dynamically during workflow

No sensitive data exists inside the repository

âš ï¸ Error Handling

For each processed row:

Column	Description
kayit_durumu	Shows Done or Error
hata_mesaj	If an error occurs, full traceback is written here
booking_id	Returned for new reservations

This makes debugging extremely transparent.

